cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel deep neural network architecture for detecting and revising adversarial examples to achieve high classification accuracy. This work involves machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it deals with adversarial attacks. The approach also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) as it proposes a new network architecture. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.CR, followed by cs.AI and cs.NE.
